# Implementation Plan: Phase 4 - Frontend Web Application

This plan details the design and implementation of **Phase 4**, which introduces the interactive frontend for the TransactSphere banking platform. The frontend will consume the REST APIs exposed by the API Gateway (`http://localhost:8080`) to provide users with a seamless banking experience.

## Goal Description
Build a modern, interactive, and visually stunning web application that allows users to register, log in, view their account balances, perform transactions (transfers, deposits, withdrawals), and read their notifications. The frontend will be built using **Vite + React** and styled entirely with **Vanilla CSS** to ensure maximum flexibility and rich aesthetics (glassmorphism, dark mode, smooth micro-animations).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technology Stack**
> As per the guidelines, we will build this as a **React SPA (Single Page Application)** using **Vite** for the build tool. For styling, we will use **Vanilla CSS** with a robust design system to deliver a premium, modern banking UI.
> Is this acceptable, or would you prefer a different stack?

> [!WARNING]
> **CORS Configuration**
> The API Gateway is already configured to allow CORS requests from `http://localhost:5173` (the default Vite development port). The frontend will be configured to run on this port.

